rComments: Awesome teacher, but you have to work! Very helpful and smart. She speaks with an academic accent?

Great and crystal clear prof, i notice that alot of bad comments were made about this prof, although not easy and requires attendance. If you listen and understand, it will be a great class, i highly appreciated this prof and consider her to be one of the best prof's at university of Ottawa

The worst professor in my 4 years at Ottawa U. She didnt show up to 2 classes,  her lectures are unbearable, her english is very difficult to understand, and teaching skills and while she may have knowledge in her field she was not meant to be a teacher thats for sure.

Unfortunately my money was wasted on her course. The subjects covered could have been developed better and more thoroughly.  My time was wasted as she rolled into class late a number of times, and half an hour late for another. If you take this course after reading this, I really wont feel sorry for you.

I agree with what somebody wrote here.. even tho u go to all the class and then you ask a question she will ask you if you went to the class..like come on...or when u miss one and she gave the midterms paper....she wotn send it via email..l...come on....if i wanna pay for a class.i rather learn things then having class about what we had to read

I personally dont like her as a teacher, you ask for help and she replies: "have you been to class" (which I assisted all the time). She talks really low in same tone which gets really boring after a while. Doesn't explains very clearly what she wants. Work load is average. Although she gets points for trying, she just doesn't have it.
She was a very unfair person.  Seemed very disintrested in even being in class.  Distracted and morbid all the time.
Great professor.  I learned a lot about Methodology from her and highly recommend her to everyone.
